special_cp.overview: Mew's has 3691 max CP (at Level 50). A Mew obtained from Raids can be encountered from 1785 CP to 1865 CP, or if weather boosted, in the 2231 CP to 2332 CP range. In Field and Special Research, Mew can be found in the 1339 CP to 1399 CP range.
more_info: Field and Special Research encounters are always Level 15. IVs range from 10 (min) to 15 (max). Field Research encounters have a 10/10/10 IV floor.
Pokmon hatched from Eggs are always Level 20. IVs range from 10 (min) to 15 (max). Egg Hatches have a 10/10/10 IV floor.
Raid Bosses caught without weather boost are always Level 20. IVs range from 10 (min) to 15 (max). Raid Catches have a 10/10/10 IV floor.  Shadow Pokmon have 6/6/6 IV floor in raids.
Shadow Pokmon have 6/6/6 IV floor in raids.
Raid Bosses caught with weather boost are always Level 25. IVs range from 10 (min) to 15 (max). Weather boosted Raid Catches have a 10/10/10 IV floor.  Shadow Pokmon have 6/6/6 IV floor in raids.
Shadow Pokmon have 6/6/6 IV floor in raids.
Wild encounters range from Level 1 to Level 30 Pokmon. Their IVs range from 0 (min) to 15 (max) for each stat.

Weather Boosted wild Pokmon encounters get a 5 Level boost, bringing their Level range to Level 6 to Level 35. In addition, they have a guaraneed minimum IV value of 4 for each stat, resulting in a 4/4/4 IV floor.

mega_boost.title: Mega Pokmon that boost Mew
mega_boost.intro_text: A list of Mega Pokmon that boost Mew's Psychic-type moves, Candy, and Candy XL from catching Mew.

bonus_info.raid_bonus: Mega and Primal Raid Bonus  Mega Pokmon boost the attack power of all other Pokmon when battling in Raid Battles by 10%. Attacks that share their type with the Mega Pokmon's type(s) receive a 30% boost. However, these bonuses do not stack if there are multiple Mega-Evolved Pokmon battling simultaneously; only the higher boost will be applied.
bonus_info.catch_bonus: Mega and Primal Catch Bonus  While a Pokmon is Mega-Evolved, additional XP and Candy is granted when catching a Pokmon that shares a type with it, or for any raid boss caught. These do not stack with each other. Additionally, High and Max Level Mega-Evolved Pokmon grant an increased chance to obtain Candy XL when catching a Pokmon that shares a type with it.

size_info.description: Mew's height ranges from 0.2 m to 0.7 m, with the average being 0.4 m. The illustration shows a comparison with a 1.70 m (507) tall Trainer. Max height has been limited to 450px for rendering purposes.

faq.question: What are Mews strengths and weaknesses?
faq.answer: As a Psychic-type Pokmon, Mew is weak to Bug, Dark, and Ghost-type moves.

faq.question: What are the best moves for Mew in Pokmon GO?
faq.answer: The best moves for Mew in Pokmon GO are Snarl and Psychic. This moveset has a DPS (Damage Per Second) of 12.163 and a TDO (Total Damage Output) of 306.129.

faq.question: How does Mew perform in Raids?
faq.answer: Mew's Raid attacker tier is currently not known, has no viable moves, or it is too low to be ranked.

faq.question: How does Mew rank as a Psychic-type attacker?
faq.answer: Mew is an F-Tier Psychic-type attacker and not recommended for Raid battles.

faq.question: What Mega Pokmon boost Mew?
faq.answer: The following Mega Pokmon boost Mew: Mega Alakazam, Mega Slowbro, Mega Gardevoir, Mega Medicham, Mega Metagross, Mega Latias, Mega Latios, Mega Rayquaza, and Mega Gallade.

faq.question: What is Mews maximum CP at Level 40 and Level 50?
faq.answer: Mews maximum CP at Level 40 is 3265 CP and 3691 CP at Level 50.

faq.question: Can Mew be shiny in Pokmon GO?
faq.answer: Mew can be Shiny in Pokmon GO .

faq.question: Can Mew Dynamax in Pokmon GO?
faq.answer: Mew cannot Dynamax in Pokmon GO.
